Police have been deployed around the Westernburg police station in Limpopo. This after angry protesters made their way to the station and torched two police vehicles on Tuesday. Residents have been demonstrating against a lack of housing and high electricity rates. The situation remains tense and all roads to the area have been blocked. “The intention of police beefing up is to make sure the security is okay and that property is protected and as police we like to condemn situation where people show emotions and become violent when there are procedures in place for people to can conduct their demands,” said SAPS spokesperson, Captain Mamphaswa Seabe. Protesters torched two police vehicles. They are demanding RDP houses and cheaper electricity. They also want a piece of land belonging to an Asian businessman to be expropriated. This morning, police had to use teargas to disperse protesters. 